data.title: Walkin' Rosie
data.text:
Eric has played in bands since high school, including Stratosphere, RC Static and Hero Atlantic and The Virtuals.

Eric's background is rooted in classic and progressive rock with a healthy love for all things 90s. Some of his favorite bands/artists include: Rush, Dream Theater, Haken, Tool, Racer X, Gin Blossoms and Queensryche.

Outside of music, Eric works as an engineer. He enjoys ice hockey, carpentry, stand-up comedy and spending time with his wife, Trisha, and dog Cooper.

Tony has played in many western PA bands over the last 30 years including DEN OF THIEVES, TOBACCO ROAD, GLITZ, ELECTRA LOVES DADDY, 4SP, 2ROCK2, FINALLY FREE and MR. SCARY. In addition to Walkin' Rosie, Tony is currently also a member of JUMPIN JACK FLASH, a Rolling Stones Tribute band. Tony comes from a wide and varied musical background that includes playing several instruments & many styles of music. His versatility and experience means that he ready to jam with anyone, anytime.

In the daytime, Tony works as a Director of Consulting Services at CGI. He and his wife enjoy supporting their son's music and performing arts interests.

Tony's lifelong love of music has had many influences, including Rush, The Red Hot Chili Peppers, Metallica, Jaco Pastorius, Jeff Berlin, & Tony Franklin. Some of his favorite bands and performers are Motley Crue, Mr. Big, Anthrax, the Rolling Stones, Skid Row, John Corabi & Charlie Haden. Tony is also a fan of television and film. Favorite shows include The Office, American Horror Story & Stranger Things, while he enjoys films such as Natural Born Killers, Airplane, Old School & American Pie.

John has performed originals and covers with several bands in the area for nearly 20 years. He has tackled just about every role that a person can in that time- guitarist, bassist, sound engineer and occasional drummer. John started on drums with his dad at a very young age but took a break from music until he picked up the guitar in college and started playing locally.

In addition to Walkin' Rosie, John still performs original music in Elliotsville Road, a band that he founded with his father. John is a huge supporter of local music and artists and really enjoys going to see his friends perform as much as possible.

Outside of music, John works at Powercast as an engineer. He loves fishing, working out, spending time with his fiancée Erin and dog Fleury, working on his house and eating bar food.

John’s favorite music artist is John Mellencamp, but honorable mentions include: Jason Aldean, Oasis, Lynyrd Skynyrd, Rolling Stones, Alice in Chains, Pearl Jam and Neil Young. His favorite songs are Simple Man, Alive, Between a Laugh and a Tear and Jumpin’ Jack Flash.

John is the lead, male singer and one of the original founding members of Walkin’ Rosie. His earliest memories that sparked his love of music start in high school when he’d attend different rock and alternative concerts.

Outside of the band, John works for Mine Safety Appliances (MSA) and some of his main hobbies include working out, fishing, golfing, spending time outdoors…and eating! His favorite past times are hanging with family and adventuring through life with his wife, Olyvia, and their cats Lilly & Olive.

One of John’s favorite artists- the one that inspired his interest in singing the most- is Aaron Lewis, who most people remember as the lead singer of Staind in the early 90’s. Some additional favorite artists of his are Pearl Jam, Red Hot Chili Peppers, Alice in Chains, Johnny Cash, Chris Cornell - and some Rebelution and Tribal Seeds when sipping a beer on the beach.

Maria is one of original founding members of WR. Her earliest memories of musical performance revolve around her father’s band, Amber, & sing-a-longs/dance parties/talent shows with her siblings. Maria’s love of vocal performance is owed to time spent in church choir & to the encouragement of her teachers & friends in the Woodland Hills School District Music Department. She remains connected to the Department as a Board Member of the WH Performing Arts Guild & through participation in a variety of alumni performances.

Outside of music, Maria manages the servicing of a book of clients for a team of financial advisors at Baird Private Wealth Management - one being her brother, WR 1.0 drummer, Joe. Her favorite thing to do is spend time outdoors with her three dogs, Diesel, Loki & Salem. She also relishes being the “cool aunt.”

Maria has an admittedly, extremely eclectic list of musical favorites/influences that include: Queen, W A Mozart, The Monkees, Genesis, Eminem, Hank Williams Jr., Boyz II Men, Stephen Sondheim, The Fugees, Igor Stravinsky, Linkin Park, Adele, Evanescence, Andrew Lloyd Webber, Justin Timberlake, P!nk, Led Zeppelin and boy bands- NKOTB, BSB & *NSYNC

Mark is a founding member of the group. Though known by most for his accomplishments on the football field, Mark played upright bass throughout his childhood and went on to pick-up rhythm guitar as an adult. As Walkin' Rosie has continued to grow its list of song covers over the years, Mark has put his talents to use learning keyboard parts.

Mark spends his days in management at US Steel's Edgar Thompson Works. He enjoys spending his free time with family and friends, at the gym and as an outdoorsman.

Mark is a fan of country and rock music and enjoys attending live music events.
